column2:
At the start of the Fight phase, you can select one friendly ORKS unit within 12’’ of this model and roll one D6: 
- on a 1, this model suffers D3 mortal wounds; 
- on a 2-5, until the end of the phase, add 1 to the Strength characteristic of melee weapons equipped by models in that unit;
- on a 6, until the end of the phase, add 1 to the Strength characteristic of melee weapons equipped by models in that unit and those weapons have the LETHAL HITS ability.

Each time this model ends a Charge move, select one enemy unit within Engagement Range of it and roll one D6: 
- on a 2-5, that enemy unit suffers D3 mortal wounds;
- on a 6, that enemy unit suffers 3 mortal wounds.

Once per turn, at the end of your Movement phase, one WEIRDBOY from your army can use this ability. If it does, roll one D6:
- one a 1, that WEIRDBOY’s unit suffers D6 mortal wounds;
- one a 2+, remove this WEIRDBOY’s unit from the battlefield and set it up again anywhere on the battlefield that is more than 9’’ horizontally away from all enemy models.

In your opponent’s Command phase, you can select one enemy unit within 18’’ of and visible to this PSYKER and roll one D6:
- on a 1, this PSYKER’s unit suffers D3 mortal wounds;
- one a 2+, until the start of your opponent’s next Command phase, each time a Battle-shock or Leadership test is taken for that enemy unit, subtract 2 from that test.
